The paper discusses Fog computing, which is a subfield of Distributed Computing (cs.DC). It also mentions the Internet of Things (IoT), which falls under the category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The paper proposes a nature-inspired architecture that utilizes algorithms and techniques from the fields of multi-criteria decision making, graph theory, and machine learning, which are all subfields of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the need for adaptive resource management, which is a characteristic of Systems and Control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper proposes a new architecture, which involves modeling the Fog as a distributed intelligent processing system, which is a topic in Software Engineering (cs.SE).
